sub_title: Product Owner at Pasha Bank OJSC | Fostering SME Growth | Economics & Business Graduate from Erasmus University
summary:
As a graduate from Erasmus University Rotterdam with a BSc in Economics and Business Economics, I bring a wealth of experience in financial roles from diverse organizations. My academic journey helped me build a strong foundation in finance, where I focused my thesis on the intriguing factors influencing cryptocurrency use in the US.

In my roles at ABN AMRO Clearing Bank, Theodore Capital, and Ernst & Young, I honed my skills in data analysis, transaction settlements, and accounts management, while also identifying and implementing efficiency improvements in accounting systems.

Leadership is a quality I value and constantly strive to enhance. Founding an event organizing group was a significant milestone in my journey, providing me the opportunity to manage, plan, and lead a team, while honing my negotiation skills.

Outside of my professional life, I'm a fitness enthusiast with a particular passion for kickboxing and tennis. I believe in maintaining a balance between professional and personal interests, and my love for sports certainly plays a pivotal role in that.

I'm multilingual, proficient in Azerbaijani, Russian, English, and Turkish. This linguistic versatility, coupled with my broad software knowledge, allows me to comfortably navigate the global financial industry.
